          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-03-26 06:56:44.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-4249 quota: fix race on setting quota lock data",
        "message": "LU-4249 quota: fix race on setting quota lock data\n\nIn qsd_intent_lock(), we set the lock data as lqe (or qqi) when\ncreating lock, and take the lqe (or qqi) reference after lock\ncreated, which introduced a small race window which can lead to\nextra reference drop on lqe (or qqi):\n\n- qsd_intent_lock() calls ldlm_cli_enqueue()->ldlm_lock_create();\n- ldlm_lock_create() created lock and set lock data succefully;\n- OST disconnect with MDT, cleanup_resource() clears all quota\n  locks, that'll trigger blocking ast on the newly create lock;\n- qsd_id_blocking_ast() drops lqe refcount;\n- ldlm_lock_create() continue and fail on lvb allocation;\n- qsd_intent_lock() fail out without taking lqe reference;\n\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Id60e1a4106ca733a6b4845e8ed1fa70775c8242d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
